events.name: Google I/O Extended 2017
events.description:
Google I/O is an annual developer festival held at the outdoor Shoreline Amphitheatre. 

I/O Extended events bring local developer communities together to experience the I/O keynotes and sessions with one another in real-time, around the globe.

GDG Cochin is happy to host Google I/O Extended on May 17th 2017. Complete Agenda will be published shortly

Please be informed that due to regulations at venue, parking would be own responsibility.

NB : Please RSVP only once you make sure you are attending, as it enhance organising and experience.

Kindly bring a printed confirmation of the event.

events.name: Google Developers :: Solve For India
events.description:
GDG Cochin is happy to have Google Developers :: Solve For India at Cochin.

Google Developers :: Solve For India

Google Developers :: Solve for India initiative aims to nurture developers, tech entrepreneurs and reach, support, mentors across India through access to open technologies, training and recommendations at networking conferences reaching the grassroots in India.

REGISTER NOW

We are excited to visit Kochi, on 05 Aug 2017, to share our thoughts on innovative technologies and encourage you to build the next mobile, web, cloud and machine learning solutions.

34/1111 N. H. 47, Lulu International Shopping Mall, Edappally, Kochi, Kerala[masked]

Come and Join us to learn, share and connect with peers and Google team. We look forward to see you at, Solve For India - Kochi soon!

Thanks,Google Developer Relations Team

Connect with us using #SolveForIndia

events.description:

events.name: Google I/O 2018 Extended - Cochin

venue.name: Lulu Cyber Tower
venue.address_1: Infopark Road, Infopark Campus, Kakkanad, Kerala 682030, India

events.description:
I/O brings together developers from around the globe for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and the first look at Google’s latest developer products.

This year’s developer festival will be held May 8-10 at the Shoreline Amphitheatre in Mountain View, CA.

We are bringing the magic of I/O to Kochi with I/O Extended where we will get the local developer community together to experience the keynote!

The event will be held at Lulu Cyber Park, Infopark

Drop by if you're ready to experience the Google I/O at Kochi.

Registration Link : http://bit.ly/iocochin18

NB: Make sure that you register in the google form and get the official invite together with RSVP

events.name: Machine Learning StudyJam 2018  (Week 1)
events.description:
Google's Machine Learning crash course based study jam organizing by GDG Cochin in association with Kerala AI Initiative and Nurture.ai
This study jam will be very focused on Machine Learning principles. A good working knowledge of Python is mandatory to be productive

Blog: https://india.googleblog.com/2018/07/the-machine-learning-crash-course-mlcc.html

Register and request for joining. Our team will get back to you on 31/7/2018.

NB: Rather than RSVP, You've to fill the google form to officially register and request for Joining. We'll email you the time and details

events.name: International Women's Day Celebration IWD'19 - WTM Cochin
events.description:
Google Women TechMakers Cochin Chapter is hosting IWD'19 to celebrate International Women’s Day. We invite all genders to join us on March 23rd at the Maker Village, KTIZ to celebrate and support the diversity in the technological industry. All passionate people out there join us to get learn, interact and have fun :)

If you’re a professional or a student who’s interested to join us in this celebration, register at bit.ly/IWDCOCHIN

Registration in the Google Form is Mandatory.

AGENDA

09:30 AM - 10:30 AM
Keynote Session by Asha Thomas Fenn, Education and Training Industry veteran

10:30 AM - 11:00 AM
WTM - Programs and Opportunities by P A Anjali & Amalu Susan Santhosh, WTM Leads Cochin Chapter

11:00 AM - 11:35 AM
Technical Talk on Big Data Analytics by Tabassum Jabbar, Software Engineer, UST Global

11:35 AM - 12:25PM
How to build and work on your career? by Shyamini Nair, QA Specialist at Baker Hughes, a GE Company

12:25 PM - 01:10 PM
Technical session on Web Scraping by Anusree S, CTO, Pehia Foundation

01:10 PM - 01:45 PM
Lunch/Networking

01:45 PM - 02:25 PM
Panel Discussion / #I’m Remarkable Workshop

02:25 PM - 03:00 PM
Technical Talk on Data Science by Haritha Paul

03:00 PM - 03:45 PM
How to stand out in the crowd? by Nikitha Mallya

03:45 PM - 04:00 PM
Group Pic/Feedback/Networking

04:00 PM
End
